4
00:00:53,787 --> 00:00:56,522
    whether it's a hangnail     
       that needs fixing        

5
00:00:56,524 --> 00:00:58,391
    or it's simply time for a   
             trim,              

6
00:00:58,393 --> 00:01:01,460
 a nail nipper is a good thing  
  to have at your fingertips.   

7
00:01:01,462 --> 00:01:03,529
 a nipper is a precision tool,  

8
00:01:03,531 --> 00:01:05,631
        one that offers         
      a bit more control        

9
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:07,133
  than lever-style clippers.    

10
00:01:07,135 --> 00:01:10,770
     the result is usually      
    a more manicured look.      

11
00:01:15,944 --> 00:01:18,143
           heavy duty           
 and made of stainless steel,   

12
00:01:18,145 --> 00:01:21,546
  the nipper nail cutter looks  
               as               
 if it belongs in a tool chest  

13
00:01:21,548 --> 00:01:24,884
   and it actually works like   
        cutter pliers.          

14
00:01:27,955 --> 00:01:29,155
     squeezing the handles      

15
00:01:29,157 --> 00:01:31,290
    brings the curved blades    
      at the end together       

16
00:01:31,292 --> 00:01:34,627
 for a well-rounded trim job.   

17
00:01:34,629 --> 00:01:37,562
       the handles offer        
  a bit moore maneuverability   

18
00:01:37,564 --> 00:01:42,101
    than the lever mechanism    
  on a standard nail clipper.   

19
00:01:42,103 --> 00:01:45,904
     production begins with     
  these forged-steel blanks.    

20
00:01:45,906 --> 00:01:49,709
     they'll make two pairs     
of nail nippers from each one.  

21
00:01:49,711 --> 00:01:51,510
      they load the blanks      
        onto a carriage         

22
00:01:51,512 --> 00:01:54,280
      that transports them      
        into a furnace.         

23
00:01:55,849 --> 00:01:57,716
  subjected to intense heat,    

24
00:01:57,718 --> 00:01:59,051
    the steel blanks become     

25
00:01:59,053 --> 00:02:01,821
    white-hot and malleable     
          in minutes.           

26
00:02:05,526 --> 00:02:08,794
       the foundry worker       
  transfers a blank to a die.   

27
00:02:08,796 --> 00:02:11,229
   he moves it across the die   
       and flips it over        

28
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:12,798
   as a hammer slams it into    

29
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:15,134
        the shape of two        
      nail-nipper shanks,       

30
00:02:15,136 --> 00:02:17,103
   each with a cutting head.    

31
00:02:18,806 --> 00:02:20,272
   it takes several strikes     

32
00:02:20,274 --> 00:02:24,210
 to create the right impression 
  on both sides of the blank.   

33
00:02:27,881 --> 00:02:31,350
   the process transforms the   
    narrow blank into a wider   
             piece              

34
00:02:31,352 --> 00:02:34,086
      with two nail-nipper      
          formations.           

35
00:02:34,088 --> 00:02:37,890
    this is the blank before    
             forging            
           and now.             

36
00:02:39,694 --> 00:02:42,895
 once the two shanks have been  
    separated and trimmed,      

37
00:02:42,897 --> 00:02:45,097
      a drill cuts a hole       
     under the blade end.       

38
00:02:45,099 --> 00:02:46,298
    this is the area where      

39
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:48,967
       the nipper shanks        
       are to be joined.        

40
00:02:48,969 --> 00:02:51,704
         a milling tool         
     shaves down the area       

41
00:02:51,706 --> 00:02:54,573
  for a neat and level joint.   

42
00:02:54,575 --> 00:03:01,447
 this is the nail-nipper shank  
    before the joint work and   
             after.             

43
00:03:01,449 --> 00:03:05,050
    they transfer the nipper    
             shanks             
    to a finishing machine.     

44
00:03:05,052 --> 00:03:07,986
 they bounce around in a stream 
  of abrasive ceramic pebbles   

45
00:03:07,988 --> 00:03:09,188
       for a few hours.         

46
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:12,558
 this rubs off the rough bits.  

47
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:15,795
     a magnetized conveyor      
  pulls out the steel shanks,   

48
00:03:15,797 --> 00:03:19,065
  leaving the ceramics behind   
     and carries the shanks     
            forward.            

49
00:03:23,537 --> 00:03:26,939
       an employee sands        
   the entire surface of each   
             shank              

50
00:03:26,941 --> 00:03:29,375
         until it looks         
      completely smooth.        

51
00:03:34,348 --> 00:03:36,348
         he brushes oil         
      onto a shank joint        

52
00:03:36,350 --> 00:03:39,684
 to prevent rust and abrasion.  

53
00:03:39,686 --> 00:03:43,355
   it's time to rivet the two   
 nail-nipper shanks together.   

54
00:03:43,357 --> 00:03:44,890
the rivets funnel into tooling  

55
00:03:44,892 --> 00:03:47,559
        above and below         
    the nail-nipper shanks.     

56
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:51,097
    the machinery drives the    
             rivets             
 into the holes in the shanks.  

57
00:03:54,902 --> 00:03:57,303
          once joined,          
  they cannot be pulled apart   

58
00:03:57,305 --> 00:04:00,840
 without completely destroying  
       the nail nippers.        

59
00:04:03,778 --> 00:04:06,578
         at this point,         
 the rivets protrude slightly   

60
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:09,749
   and could snag on clothing   
       or other things.         

61
00:04:10,784 --> 00:04:12,651
 an employee sands each rivet   

62
00:04:12,653 --> 00:04:17,790
  until it's on the same plane  
    as the rest of the nipper   
             joint.             

63
00:04:17,792 --> 00:04:18,991
     the vigorous sanding       

64
00:04:18,993 --> 00:04:22,361
      makes the rivet seem      
     to almost disappear.       

65
00:04:24,798 --> 00:04:27,199
          he polishes           
    the inside of the nipper    
             blades             

66
00:04:27,201 --> 00:04:29,668
      to completely smooth      
         the surfaces.          

67
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:31,070
        an even surface         

68
00:04:31,072 --> 00:04:33,071
 can be more thoroughly cleaned 
        and disinfected         

69
00:04:33,073 --> 00:04:35,107
      between manicures.        

70
00:04:40,681 --> 00:04:43,749
           the blades           
are still blunt at this point.  

71
00:04:43,751 --> 00:04:46,885
  the next member of the team   
    files them on an angle      

72
00:04:46,887 --> 00:04:49,155
 to give them a cutting edge.   

73
00:04:51,025 --> 00:04:52,158
filing too little could hamper  

74
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:54,627
         the clearance          
      between the blades.       

75
00:04:54,629 --> 00:04:57,730
        filing too much         
     would ruin the nippers     
           entirely.            

76
00:04:59,967 --> 00:05:01,767
    he tests them on paper.     

77
00:05:01,769 --> 00:05:05,437
   if the cutting edge slips,   
the blades may need more work.  

78
00:05:05,439 --> 00:05:08,574
  if they slice right through,  
      they're just right.       

79
00:05:10,444 --> 00:05:14,780
    next, he clamps the nail    
             nippers            
    onto a circular bench.      

80
00:05:14,782 --> 00:05:16,782
          it revolves           
    to meet up with a laser     

81
00:05:16,784 --> 00:05:19,451
  that etches the company logo  
     and other information      

82
00:05:19,453 --> 00:05:22,854
       onto the shanks.         

83
00:05:22,856 --> 00:05:25,658
  after that, they drill holes  
      and attach a spring       

84
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:29,862
      to make the nippers       
   easier to open and close.    

85
00:05:29,864 --> 00:05:33,332
      for the professional      
     who will be opening and    
            closing             

86
00:05:33,334 --> 00:05:36,334
       these nail nippers       
  a few hundred times a day,    

87
00:05:36,336 --> 00:05:39,804
   this is a nifty feature.     

88
00:05:39,806 --> 00:05:41,540
        they manufacture        
      these nail nippers        

89
00:05:41,542 --> 00:05:46,946
 in batches of 300 or 400 over  
 a period of about two weeks,   

90
00:05:46,948 --> 00:05:50,316
    so they're should always    
      be plenty on hand.        

