00:06:04,632 --> 00:06:06,999
           narrator:            
 this putter is made of jade,   

92
00:06:07,001 --> 00:06:10,569
 a precious stone traditionally 
used in jewelry and sculpture.  

93
00:06:10,571 --> 00:06:12,638
 long coveted for its beauty,   

94
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:15,240
       jade is in demand        
     on the putting green.      

95
00:06:15,242 --> 00:06:18,711
 as tough as steel with a feel  
 that's distinctly different,   

96
00:06:18,713 --> 00:06:22,348
     a putter made of jade      
   is definitely up to par.     

97
00:06:26,454 --> 00:06:27,920
   the jade putter is among     

98
00:06:27,922 --> 00:06:30,055
     a number of new clubs      
        on the green...         

99
00:06:33,928 --> 00:06:38,130
   along with crystal quartz    
  and fossilized vegetation,    

100
00:06:38,132 --> 00:06:41,533
   known as petrified wood.     

101
00:06:41,535 --> 00:06:44,603
     to make a jade putter,     
  they head for the hills --    

102
00:06:44,605 --> 00:06:49,041
    specifically, a nephrite    
   jade outcrop in wyoming.     

103
00:06:51,278 --> 00:06:56,048
  here, the putter maker finds  
     a 20-foot wide vein of     
           nephrite.            

104
00:06:58,352 --> 00:07:02,487
 this stone has taken 2 billion 
   years to form and develop    

105
00:07:02,489 --> 00:07:06,525
    a very hard and fibrous     
    crystalline structure.      

106
00:07:08,495 --> 00:07:10,229
   the carver selects slabs     

107
00:07:10,231 --> 00:07:13,832
 that are thick enough to shape 
    into four or five putter    
             heads.             

108
00:07:15,703 --> 00:07:18,037
     this one has weathered     
       to a rusty color,        

109
00:07:18,039 --> 00:07:20,439
but it should clean up nicely.  

110
00:07:20,441 --> 00:07:21,840
   the color of wyoming jade    

111
00:07:21,842 --> 00:07:25,077
   ranges from white to green   
           to black.            

112
00:07:26,513 --> 00:07:29,581
    he strikes the slab with    
  a sledgehammer a few times    

113
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:32,251
        to break it down        
  to a more manageable size.    

114
00:07:32,253 --> 00:07:36,588
    he slices through one of    
the cut pieces with a rock saw  

115
00:07:36,590 --> 00:07:41,593
 while flushing it with coolant 
  to save the diamond blade.    

116
00:07:41,595 --> 00:07:43,395
     he makes 9 or 10 cuts      

117
00:07:43,397 --> 00:07:48,600
  to rough out the triangular   
   mallet shape of the putter   
             head.              

118
00:07:48,602 --> 00:07:52,171
     he slices off the ends     
 to complete the basic shape.   

119
00:07:56,410 --> 00:07:59,144
   next, he anchors the jade    
        in a wooden jig         

120
00:07:59,146 --> 00:08:04,116
     and cuts on an angle to    
             profile            
 the sides of the putter head.  

121
00:08:05,619 --> 00:08:07,419
 he slices off a back section   

122
00:08:07,421 --> 00:08:11,757
  to give the putter clearance  
  from the ground when swung.   

123
00:08:11,759 --> 00:08:15,561
          this putter           
    has really taken shape.     

124
00:08:15,563 --> 00:08:18,030
      he removes material       
       from the corners         

125
00:08:18,032 --> 00:08:20,032
       to center the mass       
     behind the golf ball       

126
00:08:20,034 --> 00:08:21,300
   for more striking energy.    

127
00:08:24,839 --> 00:08:27,639
       he sands the edges       
   to round and soften them.    

128
00:08:27,641 --> 00:08:30,108
   he's careful not to remove   
     too much in one place      

129
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:33,045
   because that would affect    
         the symmetry.          

130
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:36,982
        he then polishes        
   the entire piece of jade     

131
00:08:36,984 --> 00:08:39,184
    against diamond-abrasive    
             belts.             

132
00:08:39,186 --> 00:08:43,222
   it's an intensive process    
  that takes about two hours.   

133
00:08:46,794 --> 00:08:50,462
 he aims a drill and cores into 
 the putter head on a 20 angle  

134
00:08:50,464 --> 00:08:54,933
         to make a hole         
    for inserting the putter    
             shaft.             

135
00:08:54,935 --> 00:08:58,937
   a perpetual flow of water    
   keeps the diamond core bit   
              cool              

136
00:08:58,939 --> 00:09:02,608
      and also flushes out      
  the little bits of filings.   

137
00:09:04,745 --> 00:09:07,546
   he gently taps the drilled   
              core              
           to jar it            

138
00:09:07,548 --> 00:09:09,615
       so it falls out of       
       the putter head.         

139
00:09:13,687 --> 00:09:16,888
       a laser emblazons        
    the product name onto the   
             jade,              

140
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:19,424
       swiftly etching it       
       into the surface.        

141
00:09:19,426 --> 00:09:24,363
 the putters can be customized  
   with a customer's name and   
             logo.              

142
00:09:24,365 --> 00:09:27,299
  he swabs gold-colored paint   
    into the laser etching      

143
00:09:27,301 --> 00:09:29,301
      to make the letters       
       really stand out.        

144
00:09:31,438 --> 00:09:32,637
      the swabbing leaves       

145
00:09:32,639 --> 00:09:34,773
    a lot of residual paint     
      around the letters,       

146
00:09:34,775 --> 00:09:36,909
      so he rubs it off.        

147
00:09:39,647 --> 00:09:41,913
   he sprays the putter with    
       a wax-based gloss        

148
00:09:41,915 --> 00:09:45,517
      to seal the stone.        

149
00:09:45,519 --> 00:09:47,853
        he then buffs it        
      against a felt belt       

150
00:09:47,855 --> 00:09:51,356
    to give the jade a satiny   
             sheen.             

151
00:09:57,998 --> 00:09:59,531
  he mixes epoxy ingredients    

152
00:09:59,533 --> 00:10:04,002
      to attach the shaft       
  to the jade putter's head.    

153
00:10:04,004 --> 00:10:08,941
       he deposits epoxy        
   in the hole in the shaft.    

154
00:10:12,546 --> 00:10:16,882
   he inserts the steel shaft   
    into the 20-angle hole.     

155
00:10:19,687 --> 00:10:22,154
     the angle of the hole      
  positions the putter shaft    

156
00:10:22,156 --> 00:10:24,556
     to match the golfer's      
        upright stance.         

157
00:10:27,828 --> 00:10:30,095
   once the pistol-style grip   
     has been slipped on,       

158
00:10:30,097 --> 00:10:34,233
   he applies a metallic-look   
              decal             
        just below it.          

159
00:10:34,235 --> 00:10:37,836
       the decal displays       
  company contact information   

160
00:10:37,838 --> 00:10:39,304
   in the event of a problem    

161
00:10:39,306 --> 00:10:42,374
  that doesn't have to do with  
    the golfer's technique.     

162
00:10:43,577 --> 00:10:45,444
after cleaning and inspection,  

163
00:10:45,446 --> 00:10:49,180
        this jade putter        
     is ready for action.       

164
00:10:49,182 --> 00:10:52,050
  putters carved from jade and  
        other materials         

165
00:10:52,052 --> 00:10:54,986
     are crafty editions to     
     the golf-club arsenal      

166
00:10:54,988 --> 00:10:58,757
     and could lead to some     
  artful moves on the green.    

